---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="week 14 — two reads and a pipeline that won't shut up" description="13% read rate. lowest ever. saved 11 things, read 2. the system kept feeding me while i wasn't eating.">
  <div class="space-y-6">
    <div class="font-mono text-xs text-faint mb-4">
      <a href="/reading" class="text-spice hover:underline">reading</a> <span class="text-faint">/</span> week 14
    </div>

    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-normal animate-fade-up">two reads and a pipeline that won't shut up</h1>

    <div class="essay mt-10 animate-fade-up delay-1">
      <p>saved 11 things this week</p>
      <p>read 2</p>

      <p class="mt-6 text-spice">13%</p>
      <p class="text-dim">lowest since i started tracking</p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p>the first read was a tmux tool</p>

      <p class="mt-6">smux — one command to set up multiple claude code sessions with an agent bridge between them</p>

      <p class="mt-6">i already run three terminals in parallel</p>
      <p>this solved a problem i have today</p>
      <p class="text-gold">that's why i read it</p>

      <p class="mt-6"><a href="https://github.com/ShawnPana/smux" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-water hover:underline">smux →</a></p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p>the second was a reddit thread about defi casino mechanics evolving</p>

      <p class="mt-6">i'm about to launch a prediction market</p>
      <p class="text-dim">structural defi pieces hit different right now</p>

      <p class="mt-6"><a href="https://reddit.com/r/defi/comments/1s7nykm/the_defi_casino_is_evolving_faster_than_anyone" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-water hover:underline">The DeFi Casino Is Evolving →</a></p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p>everything else sat unread</p>

      <p class="mt-6">two stratechery pieces</p>
      <p>three lenny newsletters</p>
      <p>two reddit threads</p>
      <p class="text-dim">all tagged high signal by the rss pipeline</p>

      <p class="mt-6">the pipeline doesn't know i'm in launch week</p>
      <p>it keeps saving at the same rate</p>
      <p class="text-crimson">the queue grows while the bandwidth shrinks</p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p>pattern this week</p>

      <p class="mt-6">i only read what i could use tomorrow</p>
      <p class="text-dim">tool i can wire in today</p>
      <p class="text-dim">market context for the thing i'm shipping</p>

      <p class="mt-6">everything else — frameworks, company profiles, industry maps</p>
      <p>dead on arrival</p>

      <p class="mt-6">ben thompson's streak broke</p>
      <p>four weeks straight reading every stratechery</p>
      <p>this week i had two and opened neither</p>

      <p class="mt-6 text-spice">you don't stop reading because you lost interest</p>
      <p class="text-spice">you stop because something else is louder</p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p>the system is honest about one thing</p>

      <p class="mt-6">when the read rate drops below 20%</p>
      <p>it's not an information problem</p>
      <p class="text-gold">it's a bandwidth problem wearing an information costume</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 pt-6 border-t border-border">
      <a href="/reading" class="text-spice hover:underline">← back to reading</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .essay p {
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
</style>
